  "page": 157,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0002",
      "text": " 138",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0003",
      "text": "d) In point-to-point topology or between NL_Ports on the same loop, buffer-to-buffer Credit is ini-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        57.65,
        540.0,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0004",
      "text": "tialized",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        69.65,
        153.51,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0005",
      "text": "N_Port Login between two Nx_Ports is complete when each Nx_Port has received the Service Pa-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        94.97,
        540.09,
        106.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0006",
      "text": "rameters of the other Nx_Port.  This may be accomplished by either implicit or explicit N_Port Login.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        537.45,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0007",
      "text": "An Nx_Port is required to Login with each Nx_Port with which it intends to communicate.  This in-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        540.06,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0008",
      "text": "cludes reserved and well-known address identifiers since they are considered to be N_Ports (see",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        540.0,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0009",
      "text": "FC-FS-2). ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        154.96,
        143.15,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0010",
      "text": "NOTE 9 – It is not required that an Nx_Port provide the same Login information with each destination Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        179.17,
        539.96,
        189.22
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0011",
      "text": "or with the Fabric.  However, an Nx_Port should avoid using contradictory or conflicting parameters with differ-",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        190.15,
        539.96,
        200.2
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0012",
      "text": "ent Login destinations.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        201.2,
        194.94,
        211.24
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0013",
      "text": "The N_Port Common Service Parameters during N_Port Login are specified in 6.6.2 (See table 150",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        226.97,
        539.95,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0014",
      "text": "for applicability).  The N_Port Class Service Parameters during N_Port Login are specified in 6.6.5",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.97,
        539.9,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0015",
      "text": "(See table 155 for applicability).  Both the Common Service Parameters and Class Service Parame-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        250.97,
        540.0,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0016",
      "text": "ters apply to each Nx_Port during N_Port Login.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.97,
        308.08,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0017",
      "text": "NOTE 10 – When an Nx_Port (A) receives a PLOGI from another Nx_Port (B), Nx_Port (A) should verify that",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        287.18,
        539.99,
        297.22
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0018",
      "text": "it is not already logged in with an Nx_Port (C) with the same N_Port_Name but different Nx_Port native ad-",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        298.16,
        540.0,
        308.2
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0019",
      "text": "dress identifier and Node_Name.  If so, it should consider the prior Login to be ended and all open Sequences",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        309.2,
        539.94,
        319.24
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0020",
      "text": "that it originated with or received from the destination Nx_Port are terminated before accepting the new Login.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        320.18,
        539.9,
        330.22
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0021",
      "text": "Such a situation may arise if configuration changes have occurred.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        331.22,
        369.78,
        341.26
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0022",
      "text": "N_Port Login provides each Nx_Port with the other Nx_Port's Service Parameters.  Knowledge of a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        358.97,
        539.94,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0023",
      "text": "destination Nx_Port's receive and transmit characteristics is required for data exchanges.  Service",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.97,
        539.97,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0024",
      "text": "Parameters of destination Nx_Ports are saved and used when communication with those Nx_Ports is",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.97,
        540.0,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0025",
      "text": "initiated.  The Service Parameters interchanged between two Nx_Ports may be asymmetrical.  Sav-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.97,
        540.1,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0026",
      "text": "ing the Service Parameters of destination Nx_Ports with which an Nx_Port communicates requires",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.97,
        539.95,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0027",
      "text": "Nx_Port resources.  These resources should be released using the destination N_Port Logout proce-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.97,
        540.1,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0028",
      "text": "dure (see 6.4",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        430.97,
        154.86,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0029",
      "text": ").",
      "bbox": [
        164.86,
        430.97,
        170.93,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0030",
      "text": "Due to the resetting behavior of a PLOGI (e.g., termination of all open exchanges with the destination",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        540.0,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0031",
      "text": "port), a port shall only send a PLOGI to a destination port if it is not logged in with the destination port.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        466.96,
        539.99,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0032",
      "text": "Examples of why a port is not logged in include:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        307.06,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0033",
      "text": "a) it has determined that a configuration change has occurred;",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        502.96,
        385.67,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0034",
      "text": "b) it has lost knowledge of the login parameters with the destination port;",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        526.96,
        431.26,
        538.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0035",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        550.96,
        114.35,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0036",
      "text": "the destination port has responded with a frame that indicates an error condition (e.g., LOGO,",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        550.96,
        540.04,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0037",
      "text": "P_RJT);",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        562.96,
        159.01,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0038",
      "text": "d) the local port has logged out the destination port, either implicitly or explicitly, due to resource",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        586.96,
        539.93,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0039",
      "text": "constraints; and",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        598.96,
        192.87,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0040",
      "text": "e) the destination port failed to respond after 2 times R_A_TOV has expired.",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        622.96,
        447.32,
        634.08
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0041",
      "text": "A configuration change shall be determined by comparing the Port_Name, Node_Name, and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        539.94,
        658.14
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0042",
      "text": "Address_Identifier received in the ACC from an ADISC or PDISC with the values previously estab-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        540.1,
        670.14
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0043",
      "text": "lished during the previous login process.  A configuration change has occurred if either ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        671.02,
        481.02,
        682.14
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p157_s0044",
      "text": "N_Port_Name or N_Port_ID do match and any of the three parameters do not match.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        683.02,
        472.62,
        694.14
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}